{"name": "implement-shipment-features", "description": "Implement shipment tracking app", "agent_type": "general-purpose", "mode": "background", "prompt": "
You are implementing features for a Blazor Web App (Interactive Auto, Global, with Individual auth) for a logistics shipment tracking company. The project is at `/tmp/sv-1bd7e8bf1d7140cbb3f4a0306e3d38d9/ShipmentTracker/`.

**Project structure:**
- `ShipmentTracker/` - server project (hosts app, API endpoints, EF Core)
- `ShipmentTracker.Client/` - client project (all interactive UI components)
- Solution file: `ShipmentTracker.sln`

**Key rules for Auto mode:**
- ALL interactive components go in the `.Client` project
- Components cannot access DbContext directly — must use HTTP APIs
- Define service interfaces in `.Client`, implement with HttpClient there, implement with EF Core on server
- Register matching services in both Program.cs files
- Don't add `@rendermode` to pages — global mode handles it via App.razor

**What to implement:**

### 1. Shared Models (in `.Client` project)
Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Models/ShipmentDto.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

public enum ShipmentStatus
{
    Pending,
    PickedUp,
    InTransit,
    OutForDelivery,
    Delivered,
    Cancelled
}

public class ShipmentDto
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string TrackingNumber { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Origin { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Destination { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public ShipmentStatus Status { get; set; }
    public DateTime CreatedDate { get; set; }
    public DateTime? EstimatedDelivery { get; set; }
    public DateTime? ActualDelivery { get; set; }
    public string RecipientName { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Description { get; set; } = string.Empty;
}
```

### 2. Service Interface (in `.Client` project)
Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/IShipmentService.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

public interface IShipmentService
{
    Task<List<ShipmentDto>> GetShipmentsAsync(string? statusFilter = null, string? searchTerm = null);
    Task<ShipmentDto?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber);
    Task<ShipmentDto?> GetShipmentByIdAsync(int id);
    Task UpdateShipmentStatusAsync(int id, ShipmentStatus newStatus);
}
```

### 3. Client-side Implementation (in `.Client` project)
Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/ShipmentHttpService.cs` that implements `IShipmentService` using `HttpClient` to call `/api/shipments` endpoints.

### 4. Server-side EF Core Entity
Create `ShipmentTracker/Data/Shipment.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Data;

public class Shipment
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string TrackingNumber { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Origin { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Destination { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public int Status { get; set; } // maps to ShipmentStatus enum
    public DateTime CreatedDate { get; set; }
    public DateTime? EstimatedDelivery { get; set; }
    public DateTime? ActualDelivery { get; set; }
    public string RecipientName { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Description { get; set; } = string.Empty;
}
```

Update `ApplicationDbContext` to add `DbSet<Shipment> Shipments`.

### 5. Server-side Service Implementation
Create `ShipmentTracker/Services/ShipmentServerService.cs` implementing `IShipmentService` using the DbContext. This maps between `Shipment` entity and `ShipmentDto`.

### 6. API Endpoints (in server `Program.cs`)
Add minimal API endpoints BEFORE `app.Run()`:
- `GET /api/shipments?status={status}&search={search}` — returns filtered list
- `GET /api/shipments/track/{trackingNumber}` — returns single shipment by tracking number
- `GET /api/shipments/{id}` — returns single shipment by ID
- `PUT /api/shipments/{id}/status` — updates status (body is the new status int)

All endpoints should require authorization (`.RequireAuthorization()`).

### 7. Service Registration

**Server `Program.cs`** — add BEFORE `var app = builder.Build();`:
```csharp
builder.Services.AddScoped<IShipmentService, ShipmentServerService>();
```
Add the necessary `using` statements for `ShipmentTracker.Client.Services` and `ShipmentTracker.Services`.

**Client `Program.cs`** — add:
```csharp
builder.Services.AddScoped(sp => new HttpClient { BaseAddress = new Uri(builder.HostEnvironment.BaseAddress) });
builder.Services.AddScoped<IShipmentService, ShipmentHttpService>();
```
Add the necessary `using` for `ShipmentTracker.Client.Services`.

### 8. Database Seed Data
Create `ShipmentTracker/Data/SeedData.cs` with a static method `Initialize(IServiceProvider)` that seeds ~8 sample shipments with varied statuses, tracking numbers (format: "TRK-XXXXXXXX"), origins, destinations, and dates. Call it from server Program.cs after building the app (use a scope, call `context.Database.Migrate()` then seed if empty).

### 9. Create EF Core Migration
Run `dotnet ef migrations add AddShipments --project ShipmentTracker/ShipmentTracker.csproj` from the solution directory.

### 10. Pages (ALL in `.Client/Pages/`)

**Home.razor** — Replace with a landing page:
- Show app title "Shipment Tracker"
- Brief description
- Two cards/buttons: "Dispatch Dashboard" (link to /shipments) and "Track a Shipment" (link to /track)
- Use `@attribute [Authorize]`

**Shipments.razor** (`@page "/shipments"`) — Dispatcher dashboard:
- `@attribute [Authorize]`
- Table of all shipments showing: Tracking #, Origin, Destination, Status (with colored badge), Estimated Delivery
- Filter dropdown by status (All, Pending, PickedUp, InTransit, etc.)
- Search box to filter by tracking number, destination, or recipient
- Each row has a "Update Status" dropdown that lets dispatcher change status
- Loading spinner while data loads

**TrackShipment.razor** (`@page "/track"`) — Customer tracking:
- `@attribute [Authorize]`
- Input field for tracking number with "Track" button
- Shows shipment details in a card when found: tracking number, status with visual indicator, origin, destination, estimated delivery, actual delivery (if delivered)
- "Shipment not found" message if tracking number doesn't match
- Loading state

### 11. Update NavMenu.razor
Remove Counter and Weather links. Add:
- Home (/) 
- Shipments (/shipments) with a list icon
- Track Shipment (/track) with a search icon
Keep the Auth Required link and the auth section.

### 12. Remove template pages
Delete `Counter.razor` and `Weather.razor` from `ShipmentTracker.Client/Pages/`.

### 13. Build and verify
Run `dotnet build ShipmentTracker.sln` from the solution directory and fix any errors.

IMPORTANT: Work in `/tmp/sv-1bd7e8bf1d7140cbb3f4a0306e3d38d9/ShipmentTracker/` directory. The solution file is at `/tmp/sv-1bd7e8bf1d7140cbb3f4a0306e3d38d9/ShipmentTracker/ShipmentTracker.sln`.
"}

